  "text": "Oximetry. Cellular oxygen consumption was measured using a Yellow Springs Instruments Model 5300 biological oxygen monitor (YSI Instruments, Yellow Springs, OH) as previously described [CITATION_1] . Cell-coated beads in 3 ml air-saturated HBSS/HEPES containing KCN (2 mM) with or without dicumarol (25 M) were placed in sealed magnetically stirred chambers at 37°C. Additions of DQ and ferricyanide to the chambers were made using a syringe (Hamilton, Reno, NV).",
